%20in%20one%20of%20his%20first%20foreign%20policy%20moves%2C%20has%20floated%20an%20astonishing%20plan%20for%20Gaza.%20On%20January%2025%2C%20soon%20after%20a%20ceasefire%20was%20achieved%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20he%20floated%20the%20suggestion%20that%20the%20US%20would%20take%20over%20Gaza%20and%20rebuild%20it%20while%20Jordan%20and%20Egypt%20take%20in%20the%20strip's%20approximately%20two%20million%20inhabitants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20during%20his%20press%20conference%20with%20visiting%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20in%20Washington%2C%20Trump%20repeated%20that%20he%20aimed%20to%20take%20over%20and%20develop%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20into%20the%20%E2%80%9CRiviera%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%26quot%3B.%20As%20his%20administration%20scrambled%20to%20downplay%20it%2C%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Trump%20reiterated%20the%20idea%2C%20clarifying%20on%20his%20Truth%20Social%20platform%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CGaza%20Strip%20would%20be%20turned%20over%20to%20the%20United%20States%20by%20Israel%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20fighting%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20have%20already%20been%20resettled%20in%20far%20safer%20and%20more%20beautiful%20communities%2C%20with%20new%20and%20modern%20homes%2C%20in%20the%20region%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CNo%20soldiers%20by%20the%20US%20would%20be%20needed!%E2%80%9C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BRemarkable%20Proposal%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20has%20called%20Trump's%20proposal%20%E2%80%9Cremarkable%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20Israeli%20Defense%20Minister%20Israel%20Katz%20has%20said%20that%20he%20has%20ordered%20the%20army%20to%20prepare%20a%20plan%20to%20allow%20Gaza%20residents%20who%20wished%20to%20leave%20to%20exit%20the%20enclave%20voluntarily.%20%E2%80%9CI%20welcome%20President%20Trump's%20bold%20plan.%20Gaza%20residents%20should%20be%20allowed%20the%20freedom%20to%20leave%20and%20emigrate%2C%20as%20is%20the%20norm%20around%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20Katz%20said%20on%20X.%20He%20has%20also%20suggested%20that%20Spain%2C%20Ireland%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20others%20opposed%20to%20military%20operations%20in%20Gaza%20should%20take%20in%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20announcement%20has%20met%20with%20wide%20condemnation%2C%20not%20just%20from%20the%20Arab%20countries%20but%20equally%20from%20those%20like%20China%20and%20Russia%2C%20Germany%2C%20Spain%20and%20Norway%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Indonesia%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20Muslim%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20suggestion%20is%20not%20without%20its%20logic.%20Trump%20is%20a%20real%20estate%20mogul%20whose%20election%20promise%20was%20to%20Make%20America%20Great%20Again.%20He%20and%20the%20Republicans%20are%20Israel's%20staunchest%20ally.%20Gaza%20has%20an%20abundance%20of%20offshore%20natural%20gas%20reserves%2C%20as%20does%20Israel.%20His%20previous%20administration%20had%20taken%20the%20bold%20step%20of%20moving%20the%20US%20Embassy%20from%20Tel%20Aviv%20to%20Jerusalem%2C%20recognising%20the%20latter%20as%20Israel's%20capital%2C%20a%20step%20much%20of%20the%20world%20has%20baulked%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHints%20From%20Trump%201.0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20Trump's%20Gaza%20plan%20has%20caught%20the%20world%20by%20surprise.%20For%20one%2C%20the%20previous%20Trump%20administration%20had%20distinguished%20itself%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20no%20new%20wars%20had%20started%20under%20its%20watch.%20Even%20tensions%20with%20Iran%20were%20kept%20under%20a%20manageable%20threshold%2C%20with%20both%20sides%20carefully%20avoiding%20escalation.%20Moreover%2C%20Trump%20had%20taken%20personal%20interest%20in%20facilitating%20peace%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20In%202019%2C%20Jared%20Kushner%2C%20his%20son-in-law%20and%20then-advisor%2C%20had%20floated%20an%20economic%20peace%20plan%2C%20hosted%20by%20the%20Gulf%20state%20of%20Bahrain.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20under%20his%20watch%2C%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20were%20concluded%2C%20which%20entailed%20the%20normalisation%20of%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20the%20UAE%20first%2C%20and%20then%20between%20Israel%20and%20Bahrain%2C%20and%20Morocco.%20Progress%20had%20also%20been%20made%20on%20the%20Saudi-Israeli%20track.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20Trump's%20recent%20electoral%20win%20is%20attributed%20in%20some%20measure%20to%20disenchantment%20with%20the%20Democrats%20because%20of%20their%20inability%20to%20broker%20a%20ceasefire%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%20A%20significant%20section%20of%20Arab%20and%20Muslim%20vote%20had%20shifted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Republicans.%20There%20was%20hope%20that%20Trump%202.0%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20facilitate%20regional%20peace.%20However%2C%20his%20Gaza%20%26quot%3Bplans%26quot%3B%20now%20may%20upend%20all%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Arabs%20Are%20Jittery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlarm%20bells%20have%20already%20begun%20ringing%20in%20Arab%20capitals.%20On%20February%203%2C%20foreign%20ministers%20of%20the%20UAE%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Qatar%2C%20and%20Palestinian%20presidential%20adviser%20Hussein%20Al%20Sheikh%2C%20sent%20a%20joint%20letter%20to%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20opposing%20plans%20to%20displace%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza.%20Egypt%20and%20Jordan%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20most%20closely%20aligned%20with%20the%20US%2C%20and%20where%20Trump%20initially%20intended%20to%20resettle%20Gaza's%20two-million-strong%20population%2C%20have%20rejected%20the%20idea.%20Egypt's%20foreign%20ministry%20has%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CEgypt%20stresses%20the%20catastrophic%20consequences%20of%20this%20irresponsible%20act%20that%20weakens%20ceasefire%20negotiations%20and%20would%20squash%20them%20and%20incite%20a%20return%20of%20fighting.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20has%20reported%2C%20quoting%20unnamed%20sources%2C%20that%20Jordan%20would%20also%20not%20agree%20to%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20Gaza%20and%20their%20resettlement%20in%20Jordan.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20existential.%20There%20is%20very%20strong%20public%20opposition%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20something%20Jordan%20can%20entertain.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20economic%20or%20a%20security%20issue%20for%20Jordan%2C%20it's%20an%20identity%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Marwan%20Muasher%2C%20a%20former%20Jordanian%20foreign%20minister%20who%20helped%20negotiate%20Jordan's%201994%20peace%20treaty%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Aid%20Carrot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20two%20frontline%20states%20that%20have%20absorbed%20millions%20of%20refugees%20generated%20by%20earlier%20Arab-Israel%20wars%20and%20are%20wary%20about%20the%20security%20and%20economic%20implications%20of%20a%20fresh%20influx%20of%20Palestinians.%20Both%20receive%20generous%20US%20aid%3A%20Jordan%20gets%20about%20%241.45%20billion%20in%20US%20military%20and%20economic%20assistance%20a%20year%2C%20and%20Egypt%20received%20%241.43%20billion%20in%202023.%20Trump%20will%20probably%20try%20to%20tie%20up%20this%20aid%20with%20his%20Gaza%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20beyond%20them%2C%20the%20entire%20region%20is%20wary%20of%20such%20mass%20displacement%20and%20deportation%20of%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20native%20lands%20and%20its%20potential%20to%20ignite%20renewed%20conflict%20and%20violence.%20All%20have%20battled%20insurgencies%20and%20terrorism%2C%20and%20some%20like%20Jordan%20and%20Lebanon%20had%20found%20themselves%20embroiled%20in%20conflict%20because%20of%20Palestinians%20who%20had%20resettled%20there.%20Almost%20all%20of%20them%2C%20save%20a%20few%20like%20Qatar%20and%20Kuwait%2C%20are%20opposed%20to%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20with%20which%20Hamas%20is%20affiliated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20states%20in%20particular%20have%20contributed%20generously%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20remain%20invested%20in%20a%20two-state%20solution%2C%20while%20also%20seeking%20to%20normalise%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20The%20UAE%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20linked%20its%20decision%20to%20normalise%20ties%20with%20Israel%20to%20the%20deferment%20of%20Israeli%20annexation%20of%20the%20West%20Bank.%20All%20eyes%20will%20be%20on%20them%20now%2C%20particularly%20on%20Saudi%20Arabia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Will%20Saudi%20Do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kingdom%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Muslim%20and%20Arab%20world%2C%20a%20factor%20that%20has%20deterred%20it%20from%20normalising%20and%20establishing%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel.%20Yet%2C%20it%20has%20also%20been%20challenged%20on%20this%20front.%20It%20also%20has%20contributed%20in%20billions%20to%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20Jordan%2C%20Egypt%2C%20and%20other%20countries%20in%20the%20region.%20In%202002%2C%20during%20the%20second%20intifada%2C%20it%20proposed%20the%20Saudi%20peace%20plan%3A%20the%20full%20Arab%20recognition%20of%20Israel%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20two-state%20solution.%20It%20has%20steadfastly%20conditioned%20normalising%20ties%20with%20Israel%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20close%20American%20ally%2C%20and%20last%20month%20announced%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20invest%20around%20%24600%20billion%20in%20the%20United%20States%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%20of%20Trump's%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%204%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20Trump-Netanyahu%20press%20conference%2C%20the%20Saudi%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20released%20a%20statement%20reaffirming%20the%20Kingdom's%20unwavering%20stance%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20issue%2C%20saying%20that%20its%20position%20on%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfirm%20and%20non-negotiable%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20it%20will%20not%20establish%20relations%20with%20Israel%20without%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20subject%20to%20negotiation%20or%20compromise%E2%80%9D.%20The%20statement%20further%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CSaudi%20Arabia%20will%20continue%20its%20relentless%20efforts%20to%20establish%20an%20independent%20Palestinian%20state%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20will%20not%20establish%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel%20without%20that.%20It%20added%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Creaffirms%20its%20unequivocal%20rejection%20of%20any%20infringement%20on%20the%20legitimate%20rights%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people....or%20attempts%20to%20displace%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20from%20their%20land%26quot%3B.%20It%20noted%20that%20this%20position%20had%20been%20conveyed%20to%20both%20past%20and%20present%20US%20administrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20will%20the%20Saudis%20walk%20the%20talk%3F%20The%20world%20will%20be%20waiting%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Aditi%20Bhaduri%20is%20a%20journalist%20and%20political%20analyst)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739514480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fr7bo1208_donald-trump-reuters_625x300_05_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrumps-gaza-riviera-plan-will-show-how-united-arab-world-really-is-7707875%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Kingdom%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Muslim%20and%20Arab%20world%2C%20a%20factor%20that%20has%20deterred%20it%20from%20normalising%20and%20establishing%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel.%20Yet%2C%20it%20has%20also%20been%20challenged%20on%20this%20front.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Ftrumps-gaza-riviera-plan-will-show-how-united-arab-world-really-is-7707875%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%