s%20traffickers%2C%20and%20other%20elements%20that%20threaten%20public%20and%20diplomatic%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202023%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%20have%20accused%20India%20of%20allegedly%20targeting%20Khalistani%20terrorists%20abroad.%20Washington%20has%20accused%20an%20ex-Indian%20intelligence%20officer%20of%20involvement%20in%20a%20foiled%20assassination%20plot%20against%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%20on%20American%20soil.%20%C2%A0Former%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20in%20September%202023%20alleged%20Indian%20involvement%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar.%20Nijjar%20was%20shot%20outside%20a%20Sikh%20temple%20in%20Canada.%20India%20dismissed%20the%20accusation%20as%20%26quot%3Babsurd.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStrengthen%20law%20enforcement%20cooperation%20to%20take%20decisive%20action%20against%20organized%20crime%20syndicates%2C%20including%20narco-terrorists%2C%20human%20and%20arms%20traffickers%20as%20well%20as%20other%20elements%20who%20threaten%20public%20and%20diplomatic%20safety%20and%20security%2C%20and%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20both%20nations%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20a%20joint%20statement%20following%20PM%20Modi%20and%20President%20Trump's%20meeting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Trump%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20presence%20of%20Sikh%20separatist%20groups%20in%20the%20US.%20While%20the%20US%20President%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20direct%20answer%2C%20he%20said%20that%20India%20and%20the%20US%20were%20working%20closely%20on%20combating%20crime%20and%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2015%2C%20a%20high-powered%20Indian%20inquiry%20committee%20submitted%20its%20report%20on%20the%20activities%20of%20organised%20criminal%20groups%20and%20terrorist%20organisations%20affecting%20both%20India%20and%20the%20US.%20The%20investigation%20was%20ordered%20in%20response%20to%20US%20allegations%20regarding%20the%20attempted%20killing%20of%20Pannun%2C%20who%20faces%20104%20cases%20across%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20India's%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20confirmed%20that%20the%20inquiry%20committee%2C%20which%20received%20full%20cooperation%20from%20the%20US%20government%2C%20had%20recommended%20legal%20action%20against%20an%20individual%20with%20known%20criminal%20links.%20While%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20person's%20identity%2C%20it%20said%20that%20action%20would%20be%20taken%20swiftly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20announcements%20from%20the%20Modi-Trump%20meeting%20was%20the%20US%20government's%20decision%20to%20approve%20the%20extradition%20of%20Tahawwur%20Rana%2C%20a%20suspect%20linked%20to%20the%202008%20Mumbai%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20which%20left%20166%20people%20dead.%20President%20Trump%20confirmed%20the%20decision%20at%20a%20press%20conference%20alongside%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20calling%20the%20individual%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20very%20evil%20people%20of%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERana%2C%20who%20was%20previously%20convicted%20in%20the%20US%20for%20providing%20material%20support%20to%20the%20terror%20group%20Lashkar-e-Taiba%20(LeT)%2C%20had%20recently%20lost%20a%20legal%20battle%20to%20block%20his%20extradition.%20In%20late%20January%2C%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20rejected%20Rana's%20review%20petition%2C%20clearing%20the%20way%20for%20his%20transfer%20to%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739511000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fvpoa47ko_modi-trump-_625x300_14_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpm-modi-us-donald-trump-big-focus-on-organised-crime-in-india-us-talks-amid-khalistan-violence-7707541%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20concluded%20a%20high-profile%20bilate